The conversion efficiency (Ƞ) of sunlight to electrical energy in solar cell devices is determined by the short-circuit current density (Jsc), the open-circuit photovoltage (Voc), and the fill factor (FF) and incident solar power (Pinc). The Ƞ can be calculated by utilizing the following Eq. (1) [19]:1η=JscVocFFPinc\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
